title: The Brit Awards 2014
description:
The 2014 BRIT Awards were held on 19 February 2014. It was the 34th edition of the 

British Phonographic Industry's annual pop music awards. The awards ceremony was 

held at The O2 Arena in London, presented by James Corden for the fourth consecutive 

year.

The statuette for the 2014 BRIT Awards was designed by Irish milliner Philip Treacy. 

Taking the form of Britannia (the national personification of Britain), the trophy 

has been redesigned by various artists since the BRIT Awards revamp in 2011.
